sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT m.site_id) 
FROM measurements m
JOIN access_logs a ON m.measurement_id = a.measurement_id;

SELECT AVG(lst_day) AS average_lst_day
FROM measurements
WHERE year = 2023;

SELECT day_name 
FROM days_of_year 
WHERE day_of_year = 9;

SELECT measurement_id, site_id, lst_day, lst_night, qc_day, qc_night, timestamp
FROM measurements
WHERE year IN (2005, 2006);

external_knowledge:
- "shadows of those mysterious locations" refers to sites with measurement data;
- "secrets recorded" indicates there are measurements taken at these sites;
- "no visitors logged in the annals" means there are no user access records for these sites.

